Package se.miun.itm.input.model.param

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AStruct
    AStruct is an InPUT structure element that combines the common information from SParam and SChoice, in order to increase code reuse.
    InPUTConstructor
    An internal representation of a constructor, which is a wrapper of the reflect.constructor class, including the information from the InPUT mapping descriptors.
    NParam
    A concrete implementation of a parameter, which represents numerical values, given their definition ranges and their evaluation engine.
    Param<AGenerator extends IValueGenerator>
    A parameter is an abstract meta description of all InPUT relevant aspects that are represented by parameter definitions, spanning e.g.
    ParamStore
    a The data-structure that manages all parameter related activities in InPUT.
    SChoice
    A structural choice element can in principle be seen as a new root to a new parameter space definition, as it represents a choice for its parameter, possibly introducing multiple new sub-parameters.
    SParam
    The concrete implementation of complex parameter meta definitions, being an extended wrapper to the SParam entry in DesignSpace.xsl.
